re is a significant part of the population that does not understand that protecting American lives over foreign lives is important. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufritzdarkweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fritz Darkweaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wedgie Avenger</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/30/01 8:57:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=78.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ending World War II</span><hr size=1> Wallace, with all due respect I believe that's a bit harsh.<br><br>Anyone has the right in a free forum to voice their opinions.  In this forum we are treating the subject with logic and debate, and I think that this process helps to both solidify our arguments and beliefs.<br><br>If we attack the values of the individual rather than the logic behind those values, we lose without even having begun.  Values cannot be argued--they are as solid and concrete.  The foundation beneath those values can be questioned, however, and the process serves to remove weak values and reinforce the strong.<br><br>Finally, the process of debate requires that all involved parties agree that each participant has something valid to say.  I may not agree with Arkitip, however I enjoy the process of debating the foundations of our values as an excercise.<br><br>And, let us not forget that values are societal rather than universal.  A Canadian-born individual will have values starkly different than an American-born individual, and vice/versa.  It is not true that in all societies it is wrong to kill.  It is not true that in all societies it is wrong to lie or to steal.  And it is through the understanding of the values of other societies that we get closer to understanding the underpinnings of our own. <p>Fritz Darkweaver<BR>Wood Elven Scout of Tunare<BR><B>1st Fist of Light</B>, emeritus<BR><BR><I>"Rich man, poor man, beggar man, thief" -- E. E. Milne</I></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showMessageRange?topicID=78.topic&start=21&stop=32>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=78.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=78.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=78.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.threadControl?topicID=78.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=78.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=78.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="firionaviefrm1">Firiona Vie General Chat<option value="firionaviefrm9">OT/OOC Forum<option value="firionaviefrm4">The 